{
  "text": "As in neutrophils and monocytes, CD157 expressed by ovarian cancer cells controls adhesion to and migration through ECM proteins. This conclusion was inferred from the observations that ligation of CD157 by means of blocking mAb: i) reduced adhesion of CD157-positive primary ovarian cancer cells and cell lines to fibronectin, laminin and collagen type I, which represent the main components of the submesothelial basal lamina (56) , and ii) inhibited tumor cell migration and invasion through ECM proteins [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "10410904"
